titlestmt.titleproper: Finding aid to the Classes of 1991-2000 records CA.MS.01028
titlestmt.author: Madison White

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2018-11-29 09:18:32 -0500.

change.item: Finding aids for each class records were combined into this meta record, with additions from recent accessions
Finding aid updated as part of the College Archives Survey

did.abstract: College Archives has been collecting class material dating back to the Class of 1879. The Classes of 1991-2000 records consist of individual class notes, examinations, papers and class letters, correspondence, photographs, scrapbooks, songbooks as well as reunion materials of the same nature, all related to or dating from the time periods during which these classes were students at Smith College.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for use with following restrictions on access: Box #'s 2301.3, 2301.4, 2301.5 - Closed until May 19, 2041 except to authors or with permission of Manja Sachet. Box #2302.3 - Closed until 2062

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Whenever donation information for a particular set of material is known, it is included in the finding aid below. However, a majority of the material was not formally accessioned and its origins are not currently known.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection brings together ten record groups that are arranged chronologically, one per graduating class. However, since some materials are placed in a class record group based on when they were created, and not by whom, materials relevant to a class may exist in more than one series.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Classes of 1991-2000 records, Smith College Archives, CA-MS-01028, Smith College Special Collections, Northampton, Massachusetts.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Classes of 1991-2000 records consist of individual class notes, examinations, papers and class letters, correspondence, photographs, scrapbooks, songbooks as well as reunion materials of the same nature, all related to or dating from the time periods during which these classes were students at Smith College.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Smith College retains copyright of materials created as part of its business operations; however, copyright in other items in this collection may be held by their respective creators. For reproductions of materials that are governed by fair use as defined under U. S. Copyright Law, no permission to cite or publish is required. For instances which may regard materials in the collection not created by Smith College, researchers are responsible for determining who may hold materials' copyrights and obtaining approval from them. Researchers do not need anything further from Smith College Special Collections to move forward with their use.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: College Archives has been collecting class material dating back to the Class of 1879. Classes of 1991-2000 records combine the student material from those graduating classes into one record group.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Class of 1991 was the 113th graduating class of Smith College.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The Class of 1991 records were processed by Tiffany Tawzer in 2007.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Class of 1991 Records contain materials describing the history and activities of the Class of 1991, including materials from commencement, reunions, and other important events. Types of materials include photographs, invitations, songs, newspaper clippings, programs, letters, and other memorabilia.
Individual biographical files are also available, and often include photographs, photo albums, newspaper clippings, letters and correspondences, and class notes.
